start

public java.lang.String start(java.lang.String dataMessage,
                              java.lang.String ecReportName)
this method start is used to start a capture session. this session can be retrieve in future call using the session ID returned. this method is frequently used by mobile device RFID reader because we can have several session in progress for a same ec report name.

Specified by:
start in interface Capture
Parameters:
dataMessage - is a message can be given by the client like bpe id
ecReportName - is the ecReport name used to retrieve class to run and to manage
Returns:
session ID

startReader

public void startReader(java.lang.String dataMessage,
                        java.lang.String ecReportName)
this method is used to have only one instance for a same ecReportName. it is frequently the case for a fix reader like a portico. so, the ec report name will be used to retrieve the instance started (there isn't any session ID generated)

Specified by:
startReader in interface Capture
Parameters:
dataMessage - is a message can be given by the client like bpe id
ecReportName - is the ecReport name used to retrieve class to run and to manage
